<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Trackit Application</title>
    <style>
        body {
            height: 100%;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .image-container {
            position: relative;
            /* create stacking context for overlay */
            width: 100%;
            height: 60vh;
            overflow: hidden;
            display: block;
        }

        .image-container img {
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            object-fit: cover;
            /* fills container while preserving aspect */
            display: block;
            filter: brightness(0.45);
            /* darken to make overlay text readable */
        }

        /* overlay that centers content both vertically and horizontally */
        .image-overlay {
            position: absolute;
            inset: 0;
            /* top:0; right:0; bottom:0; left:0 */
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            pointer-events: none;
            /* allow clicks to pass through if needed */
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .image-overlay .title {
            color: #fff;
            font-size: 3rem;
            line-height: 1.05;
            margin: 0;
            text-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
            font-weight: 700;
            pointer-events: auto;
            /* enable interaction if needed */
        }

        .image-overlay .subtitle {
            color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
            margin-top: 8px;
            font-size: 1.05rem;
            max-width: 900px;
            text-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45);
        }

        /* small screens: scale down heading */
        @media (max-width: 600px) {
            .image-overlay .title {
                font-size: 1.6rem;
            }

            .image-overlay .subtitle {
                font-size: 0.95rem;
            }

            .image-container {
                height: 40vh;
            }
        }

        .about-container {
            padding: 30px 18px;
        }

        .content {
            max-width: 500px;
            margin: auto;
            text-align: left;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #333;
            font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="image-container">
        <img src="/images/aboutus.jpg" alt="About Us Image" style="width: 100%;">
        <div class="image-overlay">
            <div>
                <h1 class="title">About Us</h1>
                <p class="subtitle">We build tools to help you track and manage your expenses — simple, fast, and
                    secure.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-container">
        <h2>About Us</h2>

        <div class="content">
            <p>At TrackIt, we believe that managing your finances should be simple, transparent, and even a little fun.
                Our journey began with a shared dream—Ojasvi Saxena and Shivankar Srivastava, not just partners in life
                but also in innovation, came together with one mission: to empower people to take control of their
                expenses and make smarter financial choices.

                As lovers and collaborators, we understand the importance of clarity and balance in life—and finances
                are no different. With TrackIt, we wanted to create more than just an expense tracker; we wanted a
                companion that helps you see where your money goes, plan for the future, and achieve your financial
                goals effortlessly.

                Every feature in TrackIt reflects our personal values: simplicity, reliability, and a touch of care.
                Because at the heart of our work lies a simple idea—finances don’t have to be stressful. They can be
                empowering.

                Join us on our journey to make expense tracking intuitive, insightful, and enjoyable. After all, good
                things happen when passion meets purpose.

                Ojasvi Saxena & Shivankar Srivastava
                Co-founders, TrackIt </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <%- include ('partials/footer') %>


</body>

</html>